        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 2:43PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 243 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 6 miles
northeast of Cass, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Dutton...                         Witter...
Pettigrew...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 500 PM CDT for northwestern
and west central Arkansas.</instruction>
